body:
# Linear Issue Management

Issues are the core work item in Linear. Every bug report, feature request, task, and improvement lives as an issue within a team.

## Sub-Skills

- **[[linear/issues/create]]** — Create new issues with all metadata
- **[[linear/issues/update]]** — Update existing issues (state, assignee, labels, etc.)

## Querying Issues

### Search by identifier

Every issue has a human-readable identifier like `ENG-42`:

```graphql
query Issue {
  issue(id: "ENG-42") {
    id
    title
    description
    state {
      name
      type
    }
    assignee {
      name
    }
    priority
    labels {
      nodes {
        name
      }
    }
    team {
      name
      key
    }
    createdAt
    updatedAt
  }
}
```

### List issues with filters

```graphql
query FilteredIssues {
  issues(
    filter: {
      team: { key: { eq: "ENG" } }
      state: { type: { in: ["started", "unstarted"] } }
      priority: { lte: 2 }
      assignee: { email: { eq: "dev@company.com" } }
    }
    orderBy: updatedAt
    first: 50
  ) {
    nodes {
      id
      identifier
      title
      priority
      state {
        name
        type
      }
      assignee {
        name
      }
    }
    pageInfo {
      hasNextPage
      endCursor
    }
  }
}
```

### SDK queries

```typescript
import { LinearClient } from "@linear/sdk";

const client = new LinearClient({ apiKey: process.env.LINEAR_API_KEY });

// Get my assigned issues
const me = await client.viewer;
const myIssues = await me.assignedIssues({
  filter: {
    state: { type: { in: ["started", "unstarted"] } },
  },
  orderBy: LinearDocument.PaginationOrderBy.UpdatedAt,
});

for (const issue of myIssues.nodes) {
  console.log(`${issue.identifier}: ${issue.title} [${issue.priority}]`);
}

// Search issues
const results = await client.searchIssues("login bug");
for (const issue of results.nodes) {
  console.log(`${issue.identifier}: ${issue.title}`);
}

// Get a specific issue
const issue = await client.issue("ISSUE_UUID");
console.log(issue.title, issue.description);
```

## Issue Fields

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `title` | string | Issue title (required) |
| `description` | string | Markdown description |
| `teamId` | UUID | Team the issue belongs to (required for creation) |
| `stateId` | UUID | Workflow state |
| `assigneeId` | UUID | Assigned user |
| `priority` | int | 0=none, 1=urgent, 2=high, 3=medium, 4=low |
| `labelIds` | UUID[] | Applied labels |
| `projectId` | UUID | Parent project |
| `cycleId` | UUID | Sprint/cycle |
| `estimate` | number | Story points or time estimate |
| `dueDate` | string | Due date in YYYY-MM-DD format |
| `parentId` | UUID | Parent issue for sub-issues |

## Pagination

Linear uses Relay-style cursor-based pagination:

```typescript
let hasMore = true;
let cursor: string | undefined;

while (hasMore) {
  const page = await client.issues({
    first: 50,
    after: cursor,
    filter: { team: { key: { eq: "ENG" } } },
  });

  for (const issue of page.nodes) {
    console.log(issue.identifier, issue.title);
  }

  hasMore = page.pageInfo.hasNextPage;
  cursor = page.pageInfo.endCursor;
}
```

## Filtering Patterns

GraphQL filters support nested comparisons:

```graphql
filter: {
  # Exact match
  team: { key: { eq: "ENG" } }
  # In list
  state: { type: { in: ["started"] } }
  # Comparison
  priority: { lte: 2 }
  # Nested relation
  assignee: { email: { contains: "@company.com" } }
  # Date range
  createdAt: { gte: "2026-01-01" }
  # Null check
  assignee: { null: true }  # Unassigned issues
}
```

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|----------|
| `LINEAR_API_KEY` | Personal API key for authentication |
| `LINEAR_TEAM_ID` | Default team ID for issue operations |
